snippet.title: Running Bot on Change Petition Using Russian IP Over 16 Hours - Amber Heard
snippet.description:
Bot for Signing on Change.org Petition over 16 hours over 2,000 times. Same Russian IP.
"Please keep in mind that the reasons why a signature might not be counted are as following:
....If someone hasn't confirmed their email address after signing -- ANSWER: Gmails don't need.
.....If more than one person tried to sign from the same device or the same IP address. -- ANSWER: IP Shuffle and Multiple Channels.
.....Their email addresses contain generic words (generic words or symbols in front of the @, such as admin, info, mail, +, -, etc)." -- ANSWER: JSON webscrapping, no symbols.

#Bots for $MONEY and its eazy.
"So even if you still use your bots, signatures will not count."
For over 16 hours, my bot signed over 2,000 times on the Remove Amber Heard from Aquaman 2 petition.
It can do 3,000 a day from ONE bot channel.
Contact me if interested in the coding.
